	</form></div><span class="pb doctop" title="page number in print edition" id="TSJN-01-06-02-pb-0197">197<a style="padding-left: 5px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=TSJN/Pages/TSJN-01-06/TSJN-01-06-02-pb-0197.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a></span><div id="TSJN-01-06-0188" class="doc">
      
      <h1>To Benjamin Harrison</h1>
      
      <div class="docbody">
        <div class="opener">
          <table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft"><span class="hi-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps;">Sir</span></td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Monticello Sep. 22. 1782.</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
        </div>
        <p>I do myself the honour of inclosing you a letter received from <span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from 'Mr.' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2010-08-02]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">mr</span> Thomas Smith as agent for <span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from 'Mr.' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2010-08-02]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">mr</span> Nathan. I have no idea that the laws, as they stand at present, can give him an action against me for assumpsits of public debts, made in council <span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from 'and' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2010-08-02]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">&amp;</span> so expressed<span class="choice addition" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Added &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2009-05-11]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">,</span> with their unanimous advice, <span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from 'and' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2010-08-02]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">&amp;</span> this in the presence of <span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from 'Mr.' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2010-08-02]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">mr</span> Nathan, who knew the debts to be public, who applied to me as a public officer for paiment, and who has never before pretended to consider it but as a public affair<span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from '. And' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2010-08-02]]&lt;/span&gt; ]"> and</span> <span class="choice deletion" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Deleted: 'even' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2009-05-11]]&lt;/span&gt; ]"><img alt="deletion" src="images/deletion_mark-trans.png" style="border:none;vertical-align: text-bottom; padding-right:2px"/></span> were it possible that the present laws should leave me exposed to shipwreck where there never was anything in the nature of a private assumpsit, I suppose it not possible they should be permitted to remain so. <span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from 'The' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2010-08-02]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">the</span> purpose of the present trouble I give your Excellency is to ask whether, should any suit be brought against me, I may take the liberty of remitting the defence wholly to the public whose concern alone it is? I had had some thoughts of abstracting myself <span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from 'awhile' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2009-06-08]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">a while</span> from <span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from 'this state' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2009-05-11]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">home</span> by a journey to Philadelphia or somewhere else Northwardly<span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from ';' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2009-05-11]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">:</span> but I suppose it would not be safe for me to leave a state by whose laws I must certainly be protected and trust myself in another where that protection would be <span class="choice addition" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Added &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2009-05-11]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">more</span> doubtful. <span class="choice addition" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Added &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2009-05-11]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">I have the honour to be with very great esteem &amp; respect Your Excellencys most obedt. &amp; most humble servt</span></p>
      </div>
      <div class="docback">
        <div class="note-source" id="TSJN-01-06-0188-sn"><p><span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from 'MS not found. Text printed from Ford, III, 601, where the letter is printed from a copy then in Vi.' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2009-05-11]]&lt;/span&gt; ]"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipient's copy ]">RC</abbr> (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ University of Virginia, Charlottesville ]">ViU</span>); addressed: His Excellency Governor Harrison Richmond.</span> The enclosed letter from Thomas Smith to TJ has not been found.</p>
          <p>On the Nathan matter, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=TSJN-print-01-03-02-0367" class="document">TJ to Board of Trade, 18 Mch. 1780</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=TSJN-print-01-06-02-0259" class="document">TJ to Randolph, 18 July 1783</a>, and references there.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div><div class="citation_box"><div><span class="bold">Cite as: </span> 
      <span class="italic">The Papers of Thomas Jefferson Digital Edition,</span>
      ed. Barbara B. Oberg and J. Jefferson Looney.
      Charlottesville: University of Virginia Press, Rotunda, 20082015. 
